    "body": "@guylouis \r\nWe have two ways to restore account at the moment:\r\n1. by entering mnemonic\r\n2. by pairing a keycard with existing acc on it\r\n \r\nThe problem with the second case is that we have to pair a card with a device before we can get master key address and check that this multiaccount already exists. We disabled the option to unpair card https://github.com/status-im/status-react/issues/9227 , and so the question is: do we want to propose user to unpair card in this case, or we just show them that account can't be restored and keep one extra slot occupied? \r\n\r\n ",
